                        <h5>CSS - Cascading StyleSheet</h5>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                After arranging the blocks of the web page dont forget you will have to paint  it and add
                                some finishing touches and <span class="extra">CSS</span> is the right tool for that
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                CSS can be added to html tags in three different ways thats is the
                                <ul style="padding-left: 16px;">
                                    <li>inline styling</li>
                                    <li>internal styling</li>
                                    <li>external styling</li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                            <div class="style-example">
                                <div class="eg-inner">
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""inline method"""
    
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;

&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div style="color: white;"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""internal method"""
    
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        .container{
            color: white;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="codeblocks">                                
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""external method"""
    
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link href="../location/file.css" &gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
