                                        <div id="color">
                                            The <span class="extra">color</span> CSS property sets the foreground color value of an element's text and text decorations, and sets the <span class="extra">&lt;currentcolor&gt;</span> value. currentcolor may be used as an indirect value on other properties and is the default for other color properties, such as <span class="extra">border-color</span>.
