                                        <div id="width">
                                            The <span class="extra">width</span> CSS property sets an element's width. By default, it sets the width of the content area, but if <span class="extra">box-sizing</span> is set to border-box, it sets the width of the border area.
                                            The <span class="extra">height</span> CSS property specifies the height of an element. By default, the property defines the height of the content area. If <span class="extra">box-sizing</span> is set to border-box, however, it instead determines the height of the border area.
