                                        <div id="border">
                                            The <span class="extra">border</span> shorthand CSS property sets an element's border. It sets the values of <span class="extra">border-width</span>, <span class="extra">border-style</span>, and <span class="extra">border-color</span>.
                                            It also splits the <span class="extra">margin</span> area from the <span class="extra">padding</span> area of a container
                                            <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;">
                                                <img width="auto" height="256" src="/img/learning/MREJv.png" alt="margin border padding">
                                            </div>
