                                        <div id="position">
                                            The <span class="extra">position</span> CSS property sets how an element is positioned in a document. The <span class="extra">top</span>, <span class="extra">right</span>, <span class="extra">bottom</span>, and <span class="extra">left</span> properties determine the final location of positioned elements.
                                            The position allows for a container to be position in a container whether <span class="extra">relative</span> i.e the default, <span class="extra">absolute</span>, <span class="extra">fixed</span>, <span class="extra">static</span> or <span class="extra">sticky</span>
                                            <br>
                                            examples
                                            <div class="style-example">
                                                <div class="eg-inner">
                                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
div{
    position: absolute;
    top: 2px;
    left: 64px;
note parent must be relative
}
div{
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 24px;
    right: 24px;
}
                                                       </code></pre>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
.sidebar {
    display: static;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
}
                                                        </code></pre>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
div{
    position: relative;
    
}
.sidebar{
    position: sticky;
    right: 50%;
    bottom: 24px;
}
                                                        </code></pre>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                        <div id="font-size">
                                            The <span class="extra">font-size</span> CSS property sets the size of the font. Changing the font size also updates the sizes of the font size-relative <span class="extra">&lt;length&gt;</span> units, such as <span class="extra">em</span>, <span class="extra">ex</span>, and so forth.
