                                        <div id="box-sizing">
                                            The <span class="extra">box-sizing</span> CSS property sets how the total width and height of an element is calculated.
                                            if <span class="extra">content-box</span> is used the width will be assigned to the content meaning any added <span class="extra">border-width</span>
                                            , <span class="extra">padding</span> area or <span class="extra">margin</span> area will be added unto the actual width.
                                            but if <span class="extra">border-box</span> is used the width given will be assigned to the <span class="extra">border-width</span>, 
                                            <span class="extra">padding</span> area and the content so only <span class="extra">margin</span> area will be added on for the actual width
